    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The salt of formic acid, sodium formate is used as a neutral buffering agent. It sometimes appears spontaneously as a layer of white crystalline efflorescence on sodium-rich glass artefacts exposed to the pollutant gas formaldehyde. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
